The paper deals with a combinatorial algorithm for solving flow maximization problems, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The algorithm is applied to market equilibrium problems, which fall under game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions convex programming, which is a topic in optimization and operations research (cs.NE), and the algorithm involves arithmetic operations and value oracle queries, which are common in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
